<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05101l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05101l">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05101l"> 101(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> adulterous / assignations</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&lsquo;The Fifth Horseman&rsquo; <font color="green">[on the Rex Ingram&apos;s Four Horsemen of the Apocalypse]</font> We next see the hero alone in his studio with the married woman. He is covering her face with passionate kisses. These secret meetings with another man&apos;s wife, which any plain man would call <mark>adulterous assignations</mark>, are styled &ldquo;harmless&rdquo; in the litterpress. Next we are shown the wife the evening after, finding the ordinary endearments of her husband insufferable. <small> <a name="TL8sep23" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TL8sep23"><cite title="source">The Leader</cite></a> (8 September 1923) 113/1-2</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
